description:
NOTE: if you use this repository, please cite the  associated paper .  
  Description  
 Analytic code for meta-analyses associated with the manuscript, "Differences in tuberculosis prevalence by sex in low- and middle-income countries over 1993-2025: a systematic review and meta-analysis." 
  Systematic review&nbsp;   
 The detailed protocol for the systematic review is registered with [PROSPERO](https://www.crd.york.ac.uk/prospero/display_record.php?RecordID=503853).&nbsp; We identified and extracted data from 117 unique prevalence reviews using [Covidence systematic review software](https://covidence.org). The initial raw data set extracted from these papers is archived in the `fullDataRaw.rds` datafile. These data include 15 surveys that did not report sex-stratified prevalence estimates, but were collected for a related analysis. 
  Data cleaning&nbsp;   
 Before analyzing the extracted data we performed various data cleaning steps. These included: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 

 revising column names and standardizing the variable values for efficient coding.&nbsp; 
 confirming no data that violated the exclusion criteria of the systematic review. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 
 ensuring no logical inconsistencies across the extracted data.&nbsp; 

 Data cleaning can be replicated by running the `cleanData.R` file using the `fullDataRaw.rds` datafile. This script will generate a clean dataset, which is stored in the `fullDataClean.rds` datafile. These data still include the 15 surveys that did not report sex-stratified prevalence estimates, but were collected for a related analysis.&nbsp; 
  Descriptive analysis&nbsp;   
 We first aimed to understand the distributions of the data we collected. We designed two scripts, `descriptiveAnalysisFigures.R` and `descriptiveAnalysisTables.R` to explore the data, in sum and within stratifications. The outputs of these scripts are saved to `outputs/descriptive` folder. 
  Meta analysis&nbsp;   
 The dataset generated from the systematic review of TB prevalence will be used to examine the differences in TB prevalence across gender (male:female) strata. In order to replicate these analyses, run `sexMetaAnalysis.Rmd` using the `fullDataClean.rds` datafile. The markdown file will call a helper function in `code/bacterialPostiveIndicator.R` that will filter the dataset down to the 102 surveys that report sex-stratified bacteriologically confirmed TB Prevalence. 
  Repository structure &nbsp; 
 ` code /` helper functions and descriptive analysis 
 ` data /` input datasets 
 ` output /` figures and tables generated by the analysis&nbsp; 
 ` supporting documentation /` includes relevant additional documentation including PRISMA and extraction form for systematic review. 
 ` sexMetaAnalysis.Rmd ` analysis of differences in TB prevalence by sex 
  Reproducibility   

 Clone the repository 
 Open the project in R / Positron 
 Install required packages 
 Descriptive analyses of the underlying data can be run by executing the scripts:  `code/descriptiveAnalysisTables.R` and `code/descriptiveAnalysisFigures.R` 
 Render the analysis document `sexMetaAnalysis.Rmd`

